print.miss

Source: R/print.miss.R
print.miss.Rd

Print method for miss objects

# S3 method for miss
print(x, fmt = "%.4f", ...)

Arguments

x

An object of class miss.
fmt

Format string passed to base::sprintf() to format proportions of missing values when printed.
...

Ignored.

Examples

library(rsimsum)
data("frailty", package = "rsimsum")
m <- miss(
  data = frailty, estvarname = "b", se = "se", par = "par",
  methodvar = "model", by = "fv_dist"
)
print(m)
#> 
#> Call:
#> 	miss(data = frailty, estvarname = "b", se = "se", par = "par", 
#>     methodvar = "model", by = "fv_dist")
#> 
#> Proportion of missingness overall:
#>  missing_b missing_se
#>     0.0040     0.0082
#> 
#> Estimands variable: par 
#> Proportions of missingness by estimands:
#>  missing_b missing_se par
#>     0.0040     0.0124  fv
#>     0.0040     0.0040 trt
#> 
#> Method variable: model 
#> Proportions of missingness by method:
#>  missing_b missing_se             model
#>     0.0000     0.0168        Cox, Gamma
#>     0.0000     0.0000   Cox, Log-Normal
#>     0.0160     0.0160      RP(P), Gamma
#>     0.0000     0.0000 RP(P), Log-Normal
#> 
#> By factors: fv_dist 
#> Proportions of missingness by 'by' factors:
#>  missing_b missing_se    fv_dist
#>     0.0073     0.0103      Gamma
#>     0.0008     0.0061 Log-Normal
print(m, fmt = "%.2f")
#> 
#> Call:
#> 	miss(data = frailty, estvarname = "b", se = "se", par = "par", 
#>     methodvar = "model", by = "fv_dist")
#> 
#> Proportion of missingness overall:
#>  missing_b missing_se
#>       0.00       0.01
#> 
#> Estimands variable: par 
#> Proportions of missingness by estimands:
#>  missing_b missing_se par
#>       0.00       0.01  fv
#>       0.00       0.00 trt
#> 
#> Method variable: model 
#> Proportions of missingness by method:
#>  missing_b missing_se             model
#>       0.00       0.02        Cox, Gamma
#>       0.00       0.00   Cox, Log-Normal
#>       0.02       0.02      RP(P), Gamma
#>       0.00       0.00 RP(P), Log-Normal
#> 
#> By factors: fv_dist 
#> Proportions of missingness by 'by' factors:
#>  missing_b missing_se    fv_dist
#>       0.01       0.01      Gamma
#>       0.00       0.01 Log-Normal
